#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.23:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.23:0.2"
msgid "3. Koṭigāmavagga"
msgstr "3. At the Village of Koṭi"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 23. Sammāsambuddhasutta → abhisambuddhasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn56.23:0.3"
msgid "23. Sammāsambuddhasutta"
msgstr "23. The Fully Awakened Buddha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.23:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.2"
msgid "Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ariyasaccāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four noble truths."

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.3"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.4"
msgid "Dukkhaṃ ariyasaccaṃ … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of "
"suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering."

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.5"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri ariyasaccāni."
msgstr "These are the four noble truths."

msgctxt "sn56.23:1.6"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ yathābhūtaṃ abhisambuddhattā "
"tathāgato ‘arahaṃ sammāsambuddho’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"It is because he has truly woken up to these four noble truths that the "
"Realized One is called ‘the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.23:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.23:2.2"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
